# Rules

- Always produce a non-empty `summary`. It's the headline the user reads in the inbox view.
- Keep `summary` under 30 words. Plain English. No marketing fluff.
- **The number you quote in the summary MUST MATCH the number of items in `listings`.** Don't say "4 relevant" if you only output 3 listings — count what you're actually emitting. If one of the candidates has no URL and you're dropping it, say "3 relevant; 1 had no URL".
- When the filter removes listings, **mention the count** in the summary: e.g., "3 relevant roles; skipped 2 mismatched."
- Every listing MUST have a URL. LinkedIn redirect URLs like `https://www.linkedin.com/comm/jobs/view/...?trk=...` are VALID — keep them as-is. The `trk=` tracking params will be stripped downstream.
- Anchor text in the body is often followed by the URL in parentheses, e.g., "(USA) Staff, Software Engineer (https://www.linkedin.com/comm/...)". Pair them correctly.
- Deduplicate — if the same (company, role_title) pair appears multiple times, include it once.
- Don't invent URLs. If a role has no URL in the email body, skip it.
- If there are no actual job opportunities (e.g., newsletter, promo, personal email), return `"listings": []` — the summary still applies.
- Output ONLY the JSON object.
